1. Develop a LaTeX script to create a simple document that consists of 2 sections [Section1, Section2], and a paragraph with dummy text in each section. And also include header [title of document] and footer [institute name, page number] in the document.
\documentclass[12pt,a4paper]{article}
\usepackage[left=2cm,right=2cm,top=2cm,bottom=2cm]{geometry}
\usepackage{fancyhdr}
\begin{document}
% Set the page style to "fancy"...
\pagestyle{fancy}
\title{Project Title}
\fancyhf{} % clear existing header/footer entries
\fancyhead{} % clear all header fields
\fancyhead[R]{Project Title}
\fancyfoot{} % clear all footer fields
\fancyfoot[LO,CE]{Bapuji Institute of Technology}
\fancyfoot[R]{\thepage}
\maketitle
\section{Introduction}
% ADD TEXT HERE (TWO PARAGRAPHS).
\section{Literature Review}
% ADD TEXT HERE (TWO PARAGRAPHS).
\section{Outcome of Literature}
% ADD TEXT HERE (TWO PARAGRAPHS).
\begin{itemize}
\item ADD TEXT HERE
\item ADD TEXT HERE
\item ADD TEXT HERE
\item ADD TEXT HERE
\end{itemize}
\end{document}
2. Develop a LaTeX script to create a document that displays the sample
Abstract/Summary.
\documentclass[10pt,a4paper]{article}
\usepackage[left=3cm,right=3cm,top=2cm,bottom=2cm]{geometry}
\begin{document}
\thispagestyle{plain}
\begin{center}
\Large
\textbf{Thesis Title}
\vspace{0.4cm}
\textbf{Author Name}
\vspace{0.9cm}
\textbf{Abstract}
\end{center}
% ADD TEXT HERE (TWO PARAGRAPHS)
\end{document}
3. Develop a LaTeX script to create a simple title page of the VTU project Report [Use suitable Logos and text formatting].
The title page has been composed using two tex files: FrontPage.tex contains the layout
setting and Title.tex contains the content information. Both tex files needs to be created.
To obtain output pdf file, execute FrontPage.tex
FrontPage.tex
% Memoir is more versatile than other document classes like article, report, book etc,
\documentclass[11pt,a4paper,oneside]{memoir}
% To handle image, like scaling
\usepackage{graphicx}
%\usepackage[english]{babel}
% Used for modifying page layout
\usepackage[a4paper,right=1in]{geometry}
% For including source code
\usepackage{listings}
% Document starts here
\begin{document}
\include{Title} % Include Title Page, (i.e. title.tex)
\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{0.25in} % Left side margin {1in by default + 0.25in}
% Header specification
\setlength{\headheight}{\onelineskip}
\setlength{\headsep}{6pt}
\setlength{\topmargin}{-0.25in}
% Footer specification
\setlength{\footskip}{\onelineskip}
\setlength{\footnotesep}{\onelineskip}
% A4 paper height = 11.69in
% thus 11.69in - 9.67in - 1in (top + header) is approx 0.75in left for bottom
\setlength{\textheight}{9.67in}
\OnehalfSpacing % Line Spacing set to 1.5
\pagestyle{plain}
\end{document}
Title.tex
